# GitHub - knocklabs/knock-node: Official Node SDK for interacting with the Knock API
created: 2021-05-05, last updated: 2025-08-06, [Read more](https://github.com/knocklabs/knock-node)

```
import Knock from '@knocklabs/node';
const client = new Knock({
apiKey: process.env['KNOCK_API_KEY'], // This is the default and can be omitted
});
const response = await client.workflows.trigger('dinosaurs-loose', {
recipients: ['dnedry'],
...
});
...
The SDK provides functionality to sign authentication tokens for client-side requests, such as for in-app feeds.
This feature requires the `jose` package as an optional peer dependency.
...
import Knock from '@knocklabs/node';
// Generate a JWT token for a user
const token = await Knock.signUserToken('user-1');
```
...
To make requests to undocumented endpoints, you can use `client.get`, `client.post`, and other HTTP verbs.
...
To make requests using undocumented parameters, you may use `// @ts-expect-error` on the undocumented
parameter.
...
To access undocumented response properties, you may access the response object with `// @ts-expect-error` on
the response object, or cast the response object to the requisite type.
Like the request params, we do not
validate or strip extra properties from the response from the API.
...
options to requests:

# knock-node/README.md at main · knocklabs/knock-node
created: 2021-05-05, last updated: 2025-06-02, [Read more](https://github.com/knocklabs/knock-node/blob/main/README.md)

```
import Knock from '@knocklabs/node';
const client = new Knock({
apiKey: process.env['KNOCK_API_KEY'], // This is the default and can be omitted
});
async function main() {
const response = await client.workflows.trigger('dinosaurs-loose', {
recipients: ['dnedry'],
data: { dinosaur: 'triceratops' },
});
console.log(response.workflow_run_id);
}
main();
...
This library includes TypeScript definitions for all request params and response fields.
You may import and use them like so:
```
import Knock from '@knocklabs/node';
const client = new Knock({
apiKey: process.env['KNOCK_API_KEY'], // This is the default and can be omitted
});
async function main() {
const user: Knock.User = await client.users.get('dnedry');
}
main();
...
If you want to set custom
```
fetch
```
options without overriding the
```
fetch
```
function, you can provide a
```
fetchOptions
```
object when instantiating the client or making a request.
(Request-specific options override client options.)

# A toolkit for working with Knock in Agent workflows.
created: 2025-03-31, last updated: 2025-10-04, [Read more](https://github.com/knocklabs/agent-toolkit)

```
// Pass all tools
npx -y @knocklabs/agent-toolkit -p local-mcp --tools="*"
// Specific category
npx -y @knocklabs/agent-toolkit -p local-mcp --tools "workflows.*"
// Specific tools
npx -y @knocklabs/agent-toolkit -p local-mcp --tools "workflows.triggerWorkflow"
```
...
```
npx -y @knocklabs/agent-toolkit -p local-mcp --workflows comment-created activate-account
```
...
permissions: {
workflows: { read: true, run: true, manage: true },
...
const toolkit = await createKnockToolkit({
serviceToken: "knock_st_",
permissions: {
// (optional but recommended): Set the permissions of the tools to expose
workflows: { read: true, run: true, manage: true },
},
userId: "10",
});
...
